NAME
    cut - remove sections from each line

SYNOPSIS
    cut -d<delim> -f<fields> [file]
    cut -c<chars> [file]

DESCRIPTION
    Extracts portions of each line from a file or stdin.
    Can extract by field (with delimiter) or by character position.

OPTIONS
    -d DELIM    Use DELIM as field delimiter (default: tab)
    -f FIELDS   Select fields (1-indexed)
    -c CHARS    Select characters (1-indexed)

    Fields and characters can be:
    - Single: -f1
    - Multiple: -f1,3,5
    - Range: -f1-3
    - Combined: -f1-3,5,7

EXAMPLES
    echo "a,b,c" | cut -d, -f2
        Output: b

    cat file | cut -d: -f1,3
        Extract fields 1 and 3

    cat file | cut -c1-10
        Extract first 10 characters

    ls -l | cut -c1-10
        Extract permission bits

SEE ALSO
    grep, tr, sort
